Baringo Senator Gideon Moi has asked the country's top leaders to leave a legacy of a united and cohesive nation. Senator Moi expressed displeasure with early political campaigns ahead of the 2022 elections, saying the premature campaigns will divide the country. He was speaking in Sugoi where he met a group of opinion leaders from Uasin Gishu and Kakamega Counties at the home of businessman and close ally of the Mois’ Sammy Kogo.